        "caption": "photo credit: Audi"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Other companies could see opportunity as European automakers shift their product strategy to make EU regulators happy. It could turn out that the new vehicle offerings on different continents might differ even more than they do now, creating an interesting situation for the future of automobiles worldwide. In fact, these stringent regulations could mean few Europeans will be able to afford cars, restricting their freedom in many ways.",
