            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "It seems like these days the trendy thing to do is declare internal combustion engines are bad and electrification is the future, despite the vast majority of vehicles on the road requiring gas or diesel to run. Even if electrification turns out to be the future of transportation, it will take a long time, maybe even decades, to switch over. Elon Musk, the great promoter of EVs, agrees with this assessment. So is this really a wise move by Audi? Time will tell.",
